<subSubSection id="6269775FCA5C8A89694B80FEC0D0ED7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3CD38457C79EFE3342576C092AB68D35" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66E3F5FE3F4133C5622CB37165490369" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This new species is the nearest to 
<taxonomicName id="0EFC88C229A093266E56AFEDAB63B7F5" genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis id="F6AB3842D9089D9612088DCD424F2EA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Briet, 1917) but can be distinguished by the shape of pronotal marking: 
<taxonomicName id="3E93F78ED3627B33E8A17CFCC423FFF5" genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis id="12B16340FEC8F437218AD9150D4AB1D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the metallic blue marking rhombic, whereas in the new species this marking is not. Additionally, the anterior margin of the clypeus in the new species is yellowish brown but black in 
<taxonomicName id="C9505B78D3AEC971E775AF5F3BCEE8CE" genus="S." lsidName="S. flavilabris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavilabris">
<emphasis id="2FF2058AA1D8D6F0B9D4BA398946B59F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. flavilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
